                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The United Nations Security Council held its 497th meeting on September 7 from 11
                    a. m. to 6:50 p. m.; see U.N. document S/PV.497. The Council rejected the Soviet
                    draft resolution condemning United States bombing in Korea (S/1679; for the
                    text, see the editorial note on the 484th Security Council meeting of August 8,
                        <ref target="#pg_546">page 546</ref>). The vote was 1 (Union of Soviet
                    Socialist Republics) in favor to 9 (including the United States) opposed, with 1
                    (Yugoslavia) abstention.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
